The evidence with the title 'Unemployment is low but more workers are leaving the workforce ... ' says Jul 16, 2015  ... The U.S. economy has created 11.5 million new jobs during the last 57 consecutive months of domestic labor force expansion .  ... So although the unemployment rate ticked down to a seven - year low of 5.3 percent in june, that number did n't do justice to the 640,000 individuals who exited the labor market  ... 
